PublicDescription: Counts cycles when frontend could not send any micro-operations to the woke rename stage because of frontend resource stalls caused by fetch memory latency or branch prediction flow stalls. All the woke frontend slots were empty during the woke cycle when this event counts.

Counts cycles whenever the woke rename unit is unable to send any micro-operations to the woke backend of the woke pipeline because of backend resource constraints. Backend resource constraints can include issue stage fullness, execution stage fullness, or other internal pipeline resource fullness. All the woke backend slots were empty during the woke cycle when this event counts.
